The current pipeline runs dual supervisor review (Claude Sonnet + Codex) for every task. Replace with a single DeepSeek verification via ClawRouter, retaining Claude only for 'audit' tasks.

Find the supervisor review loop — it is called after CodingAgent.execute() completes. Look for:
  const review1 = await this.supervisor.review(...);
  const review2 = await this.supervisor2.review(...);
or similar dual-review calls.

Replace the dual review with a new verifyTask() helper. Add this function BEFORE the main Swarm class (or wherever the supervisor calls happen):

  async function verifyTask(
    task: AgentTask,
    generatedCode: string,
    supervisor: SupervisorAgent,
    callAnthropicCachedFn: (prompt: string, systemPrompt: string) => Promise<any>
  ): Promise<ReviewResult> {
    // Audit tasks always use Claude for review
    if (task.task_type === 'audit') {
      return callAnthropicCachedFn(
        `Review this code for security and correctness:\n${generatedCode.slice(0, 6000)}`,
        'You are a security auditor. Return JSON with verdict APPROVED or REJECTED.'
      );
    }

    // Standard tasks: DeepSeek via ClawRouter (~$0.02, down from ~$0.07 dual review)
    const useClawRouter = process.env.USE_CLAWROUTER === 'true';
    if (useClawRouter) {
      try {
        const reviewPrompt = `Review this code for task: ${task.id}\nTask: ${task.description}\nCode:\n${generatedCode.slice(0, 5000)}\n\nRespond in JSON: {"verdict": "APPROVED|REJECTED", "score": 0-100, "summary": "brief summary", "issues": [], "strengths": []}`;
        const crResult = await callClawRouter({
          model: 'deepseek/deepseek-chat',
          prompt: reviewPrompt,
          systemPrompt: 'You are a code reviewer. Respond ONLY with valid JSON.',
          maxTokens: 1000,
        });
        walletState.spentThisMonth += crResult.costUsdc;
        const jsonMatch = crResult.content.match(/\{[\s\S]*\}/);
        if (jsonMatch) return JSON.parse(jsonMatch[0]);
      } catch {
        // ClawRouter failed — fall through to Claude supervisor
      }
    }

    // Fallback: single Claude supervisor (not dual)
    return supervisor.review(task, generatedCode);
  }

Then in the main task execution loop, replace the dual-review call with a call to verifyTask().

IMPORTANT: Do NOT delete the SupervisorAgent or Supervisor2Agent classes — keep them for fallback and audit tasks. Only change where they are called in the pipeline.

